<title>CANADA: Toronto stock trading to resume before noon.</title>
<headline>Toronto stock trading to resume before noon.</headline>
<dateline>TORONTO 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Toronto Stock Exchange said on Tuesday it will re-open computer trading before 1200 EST/1700 GMT.</p>
<p>The TSE said the shut-down, which occured at 1054 EST/1554 GMT, was &quot;due to the unprecedented number of orders at the re-opening of trading in Bre-X Minerals Ltd.&quot;</p>
<p>A total of 7.78 million Bre-X shares changed hands in the first 22 minutes of trading after the exchange reopened trading in the stock at 1030 EST/1530 GMT.</p>
<p>((Reuters Toronto Bureau (416) 941-8100))</p>
